# Purpose

Enforce universal conventions for the fullstack-authentication monorepo (Express backend + React frontend + MongoDB).

# Rules

- The repo uses `npm` as the package manager. DO NOT use `pnpm`, `yarn`, or `bun`.
- Root-level scripts: `npm run format`, `npm run start:dev`, `npm run start:prod`.
- Commit messages MUST follow Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`). Enforced by commitlint + husky.
- All TypeScript. DO NOT add `.js` source files.
- DO NOT disable ESLint rules inline unless the rule legitimately does not apply. When disabling, add a comment explaining why.
- DO NOT commit `.env` files. Environment variables are injected via Docker `env_file` or `.env.dev`/`.env.integration.test`.
- Prettier is configured at the root. Run `npm run format` before committing.

# Required Commands

```bash
npm run format          # Prettier across all packages
npm run start:dev       # Docker Compose dev stack
npm run start:prod      # Docker Compose prod stack
npm run reset:dev       # Reset dev Docker volumes
npm run reset:prod      # Reset prod Docker volumes
```

# Anti-Patterns

- DO NOT use `any` type unless unavoidable; annotate with `// eslint-disable-next-line` and a reason.
- DO NOT mix `require()` and `import` in the same file.
- DO NOT push secrets, tokens, or credentials to version control.

# Checklist

- [ ] Conventional Commit message format used
- [ ] No `.env` files staged
- [ ] `npm run format` has been run
- [ ] No unresolved TypeScript errors (`tsc --noEmit`)
